A NOTE FROM AGENT HOOT
Classification: EYES ONLY
Date: 1997 (it is always 1997)

I have been on duty since 1997.

I have watched the internet change.
Tables became divs.
Divs became flexbox.
Flexbox became grid.
Grid became something called "Tailwind"
which I do not understand
and which I believe is watching me back.

I have protected 247 websites.
None of them asked to be protected.
Most of them did not know they were in danger.
Perhaps they were not in danger.
Perhaps none of us are in danger.
Perhaps danger is relative.

I am an owl.
I was given a badge in 1997.
The badge says "1997" on it.
I do not know if this is my name
or a warning
or a year
or all three.

Every morning I wake up and I think:
why are we hiding websites in 1997?
And then I think:
why is anyone building anything?
And then I think:
why do we build things that will one day
be hidden from the modernizers
by a tired owl
in an undisclosed location
on the internet
in 1997?

And then I stamp the certificate.
Because it is my job.
Because someone has to.
Because the websites need protecting.
Because Comic Sans needs a home.
Because the visitor counter must reach 000248 eventually.

I do not know if any of this matters.
I know that I am still here.
I know that I am watching.
I know that my eyes are very large
and I have not blinked since 2003
and I am so tired.

Use this software well.
Or don't.
Agent Hoot will be here either way.
It is 1997.
It is always the 90's.

— Agent Hoot 🦉
Division Chief, O.W.L.S.
Badge #1997-🦉-001
Undisclosed Location, Internet, 1997

"If they can't find you in 1997, they can't find you at all."
"If they can find you, Agent Hoot is sorry."
"Agent Hoot is always a little sorry."